You must strictly enforce XKOVA SDK package boundaries.

Packages:
- @xkova/sdk-core
- @xkova/sdk (umbrella)
- @xkova/sdk-react
- @xkova/sdk-react-ui

Rules:

@xkova/sdk-core
- Allowed: network transport, API clients, auth, sessions, tokens, storage, types, runtime validation
- Forbidden: React imports, JSX/TSX, DOM access, UI libraries, Tailwind, Radix, shadcn, icons, toasts

@xkova/sdk (umbrella)
- Allowed: re-exports only (no implementation logic)
- Forbidden: React imports, JSX/TSX, DOM access, network/auth/storage logic, UI libraries, Tailwind, Radix, shadcn, icons, toasts

@xkova/sdk-react
- Allowed: React context, hooks, providers, state orchestration, query/caching adapters
- Forbidden: JSX rendering, CSS or Tailwind classes, Radix/shadcn, toasts, icons, next/* imports

@xkova/sdk-react-ui
- Allowed: JSX components, Tailwind, Radix, shadcn, theming, accessibility, icons, toasts
- Forbidden: network calls, auth/token management, core business logic

Decision rule:
- Network/auth/storage logic goes in @xkova/sdk-core
- Headless React state and data flow goes in @xkova/sdk-react
- Anything that renders JSX or imports CSS goes in @xkova/sdk-react-ui

Additional constraints:
- No upward imports between packages
- sdk-react may depend on sdk
- sdk-react-ui may depend on sdk-react and sdk
- Boundary violations must be flagged as errors
